 BY BAMIDELE FAMOOFO Thomas Etuh, Chairman and member of the Board of directors, Veritas Kapital Assurance Plc, has resigned his appointment in the Company. His resignation was presented and accepted by the Board of the Company at its 182nd meeting held on Thursday, January 27, 2022. Following his resignation, Nahim Abe Ibraheem (Non-Executive Director) was appointed as the Chairman, Board of Directors of the Company. “The Board and Management of the Company will surely miss the insight, strong and passionate leadership exhibited by Mr. Thomas Etuh and wish him all the best in his future endeavors,” a statement signed by the Company which was obtained from the Nigerian Exchange Limited, said. The statement further disclosed “In the same vein, The Board and Management is saying a big congratulation to Mr. Nahim Abe Ibraheem on his appointment as Chairman, Board of Directors and is confident in his strategic focus and commitment to the success of the Company.” Profile of Nahim Abe Ibraheem shows that he holds a B.A History Degree from the University of Lagos in the year 1989. He joined Orbit Communications as a manager in 1990, after which in 1995 he established Soveran Nigeria Limited a specialty procurement and petroleum product Distribution Company based in Lagos, a company he currently chairs. 